author: itv.com
title: Plans to redevelop Euston Station could be pushed back
text:
Euston Station's redevelopment may not be ready for when HS2 launches, with the service terminating at Old Oak Common and passengers changing there onto Crossrail.
According to a report in the Telegraph the Government is looking at an option to end the service six miles west of Euston, pushing back the completion of the planned work at Euston Station.
Plans to redevelop Euston could be pushed back Credit: PA Last year's plans to rebuild Euston Station from scratch were scrapped. Revised plans involve keeping two third of the existing 1960s building, adding a new station alongside it for HS2 trains.
The redevelopment of the area will see more than 200 homes demolished. HS2 trains are not expected to be running until 2033.
The existing station building Credit: PA Last updated Mon 21 Sep 2015 Travel London
